#SHL – GenAI Assessment Recommendation System

Developed by Rahul Rao

#Overview

This project is an intelligent Assessment Recommendation System built to recommend the most relevant SHL Individual Test Solutions based on a natural language hiring query or job description.

Instead of simple keyword matching, the system uses semantic embeddings and vector similarity search to understand the intent and context of the query before generating recommendations.

#Problem Statement

Recruiters and hiring managers often rely on keyword searches to find suitable assessments. This process can be inefficient and may not capture the true intent of the hiring requirement.

This system improves the process by:

Understanding the hiring query semantically

Retrieving relevant SHL assessments based on contextual similarity

Ensuring balanced recommendations across skill domains

Evaluating recommendation quality using Recall@10

#Solution Architecture

The system follows a structured retrieval-based pipeline.

1. Data Ingestion

SHL product catalog pages are processed

Only Individual Test Solutions are retained

Pre-packaged job solutions are excluded

Metadata extracted:

Assessment Name

URL

Description

Test Type

Duration

Adaptive Support

Remote Support

2. Embedding Generation

Assessment descriptions and user queries are converted into dense vector embeddings using a sentence-transformer model.

This enables contextual similarity comparison instead of keyword matching.

3. Vector Similarity Search

Cosine similarity is used to retrieve the most relevant assessments

A Nearest Neighbors index enables efficient top-K retrieval

Top candidates are ranked based on similarity score

4. Balanced Recommendation Logic

When a query spans multiple domains (e.g., technical and behavioral skills), the system ensures a balanced mix of assessment types such as:

Knowledge & Skills

Personality & Behavior

Competencies

This improves recommendation relevance and fairness.

5. Evaluation

The system is evaluated using labeled training queries.

Metric Used: Recall@10

Recall@10 measures whether relevant assessments appear within the top-10 recommendations for a given query.

This ensures measurable and objective validation of system performance.

API Endpoints
Health Check

GET /health

Response:

{
  "status": "healthy"
}
Recommendation Endpoint

POST /recommend

Request:

{
  "query": "Hiring a Java developer with strong collaboration skills"
}

Response includes:

name

url

description

duration

adaptive_support

remote_support

test_type

